@Node "DunderDir" "DunderDir.Guide/DunderDir"

DUNDERDIR:
 Why another dir utility? Well.. i never uses the Workbench,
 so i needed a good dir utility and did not think DIR and LIST
 was special great and other dirutilitys i have seen has not been
 good  enough, or they have been so bad i just deleted them
 right away.

 But now when DunderDir is around, everything is just great =)
 and it will be even more greater very soon.

 Now you can
 -----------

   * Configurate the output almost however you want to
     with 13 variables and a lot of option :)

   * An extra variable is also supported for you to
     save any option in so you don't have to write
     them on the command line everytime.

   * It uses the LFORMAT string(no dirutility is a truely
     dirutility without it), and you can use C text options
     ex. \n or \f :)

   * Execute the LFormat string directly instead of redirecting
     the output to file first.

   * You can list with columns.

   * You can select the length of the columns.

   * Choose any date format supported by AmigaDOS.

   * Hide files with -h bit set or starting with a dot
     or ending with .info just specifying an option :)

   * Sort after name(default), date, size, diskkey, comment
     or don't sort at all.

   * You can count the size for a directory and all the
     subdirectorys it got.

   * It can be made resident.

   * It's 100% Assembly :)


 You will be able to
 -------------------

   * Build a dirtree

   * Sorting after extension.

   * Your idea :-)


 As you can see this is the true replacement for both of the
 programs DIR and LIST :)

 I hope you will enjoy my english, it really is great(NOT) :)


                That's all folks ;)
                   Jimmie Matsson!

@EndNode

